StreetEasy Data

library(tidyverse)
library(tseries)
library(forecast)
library(TSA)
library(dplyr)
# source: https://streeteasy.com/blog/data-dashboard/?agg=Total&metric=Inventory&type=Rentals&bedrooms=Any%20Bedrooms&property=Any%20Property%20Type&minDate=2010-01-01&maxDate=2022-12-01&area=Flatiron,Brooklyn%20Heights

# note that we can also get breakdown by bedrooms if we want

# rental index - one for each of four real boroughs
rental_index_raw <- read.csv("rentalIndex_All.csv")
rental_index_manhattan <- ts(rental_index_raw$Manhattan,start=c(2007,1),frequency=12)
tsdisplay(rental_index_manhattan)


# median asking rent - four real boroughs + 155 neighborhoods
median_rent_raw <- read.csv("medianAskingRent_All.csv")
median_rent_manhattan <- median_rent_raw %>% filter(areaName=="Manhattan") %>% unlist() %>% as.numeric() %>% na.omit() %>% ts(start=c(2010,1),frequency=12)
Warning in na.omit(.) : NAs introduced by coercion
tsdisplay(median_rent_manhattan)


# rental inventory - four real boroughs + 155 neighborhoods
inventory_raw <- read.csv("rentalInventory_All.csv")
inventory_manhattan <- inventory_raw %>% filter(areaName=="Manhattan") %>% unlist() %>% as.numeric() %>% na.omit() %>% ts(start=c(2010,1),frequency=12)
Warning in na.omit(.) : NAs introduced by coercion
tsdisplay(inventory_manhattan)
